Stoner 63 was a modular light machine gun developed by Eugene Stoner the same man who developed the AR/M4 platform. The 63 was a uniquely modular weapon, you could configure it in multiple ways from light machine gun to smaller carbine sized, mag fed or belt. It was very popular among Navy SEALs in Vietnam because a few men could wield the firepower of a full sized platoon. The military never adapted it fully because it had so many working parts to maintain which isn‚Äôt ideal for the average soldier. But the SEALs loved the 63.
